doc.ContractDescription: THE PENNSYLVANIA SPACE GRANT CONSORTIUM (PSGC) SPONSORS ACTIVITIES AND DESIGNS PROGRAMMING TO SUPPORT THE MISSION OF THE NATIONAL SPACE GRANT COLLEGE AND FELLOWSHIP PROGRAM. THE MISSION OF THEPSGC IS TO EXPAND OPPORTUNITIES FOR PENNSYLVANIANS TO LEARN ABOUT AND PARTICIPATE IN NASA'S AERONAUTICS AND SPACE PROGRAMS BY SUPPORTING AND ENHANCING STEM EDUCATION, RESEARCH, AND OUTREACH PROGRAMS. OUR CONSORTIUM STRATEGIC PLAN WAS DERIVED FROM THE NATIONAL SPACE GRANT IMPLEMENTATION PLAN. THE VARIOUS PROGRAMS AT OUR LEAD INSTITUTION AND AT THE AFFILIATE CAMPUSES ARE DESIGNED TO SUIT THE INDIVIDUAL STRENGTHS OF THOSE INSTITUTIONS, WHILE COMPLIMENTING THE PSGC STRATEGIC GOALS AND CONSIDERING THE NEEDS OF THE COMMONWEALTH. OUR PROGRAMMING EMPHASIZES SUPPORT FOR NASA-RELATED UNDERGRADUATE AND GRADUATE STUDENT RESEARCH BY SUPPORT OF FELLOWSHIPS, SCHOLARSHIPS, AND HIGHER EDUCATION PROGRAMS. WE ALSO SUPPORT A SMALL NUMBER OF PRECOLLEGE PROGRAMS SUCH AS TEACHER PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT WORKSHOPS. DIVERSITY IS ALWAYS A CONSIDERATION IN PROGRAMMING AS WE STRIVE TO ENGAGE MORE STUDENTS FROM MINORITY AND UNDERREPRESENTED POPULATIONS IN THE STEM FIELDS. ACROSS THE COMMONWEALTH, WE AIM TO INVEST OUR SPACE GRANT RESOURCES PRIMARILY IN HIGHER EDUCATION AND RESEARCH INFRASTRUCTURE PROGRAMS, BUT ALSO TO LEVERAGE THE EXPERTISE AT OUR COLLEGES AND UNIVERSITIES TO SERVE THE PRECOLLEGE AND GENERAL PUBLIC COMMUNITIES. PLEASE SEE APPENDIX C FOR D FOR CONSORTIUM GOALS, OBJECTIVES AND PART MEASURES. THE GOALS OF OUR CONSORTIUM ARE TO: DEVELOP AND PROMOTE OPPORTUNITIES FOR UNDERGRADUATE AND GRADUATE STUDENTS TO PARTICIPATE IN RESEARCH AND DISCOVERY, INCLUDING STUDENT FLIGHT PROJECTS; INCLUDE PROGRAMS WITH A FOCUS ON ENHANCING THE PARTICIPATION OF STUDENTS FROM UNDERREPRESENTED GROUPS. PROVIDE GRADUATE AND UNDERGRADUATE TRAINING IN NASA-RELATED FIELDS THROUGH THE MECHANISM OF FELLOWSHIP AND SCHOLARSHIP AWARDS; INCREASE THE NUMBER OF AWARDS TO STUDENTS FROM UNDERREPRESENTED GROUPS. SUPPORT THE DEVELOPMENT OF INTERDISCIPLINARY COURSES, CURRICULA, AND WORKSHOPS, INCLUDING INTRODUCTORY COURSES DESIGNED FOR UNDERGRADUATE STUDENTS NOT MAJORING IN SCIENTIFIC OR TECHNOLOGICAL DISCIPLINES. MODEL DIVERSITY IN SPACE GRANT LEADERSHIP, PROGRAMS, AND ACTIVITIES; IMPLEMENT PROGRAMS TARGETED AT INCREASING THE RETENTION RATE OF STUDENTS FROM UNDERREPRESENTED GROUPS IN SCIENCE AND ENGINEERING. PROVIDE INFORMATION AND PROGRAMS TO INCREASE ACCESS TO THE EXCITEMENT, KNOWLEDGE, AND TECHNOLOGY FROM AMERICA'S EARTH, AIR AND SPACE PROGRAMS; ESTABLISH PSGC AS A VIABLE STATE RESOURCE AND CATALYST FOR AEROSPACE RESEARCH, EDUCATION, AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT. CULTIVATE A STATEWIDE NETWORK OF PARTNERS FROM UNIVERSITIES, INDUSTRY, MUSEUMS, SCIENCE CENTERS, STATE AND LOCAL AGENCIES TO PURSUE AEROSPACE RESEARCH, EDUCATION, AND ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT GOALS. DEVELOP EARTH, AIR, AND SPACE PROGRAMS TO ENHANCE PUBLIC SCIENTIFIC LITERACY AND TO COMPLEMENT COMMUNITY NEEDS.
